Citation.sAbstract: The experiment for the gaseous pvT property of HFO-1234ze(E) (trans-1,3,3,3-Tetrafluoropropene) was conducted with the Burnett method. The temperature range is from (318 to 401) K and the pressure is up to 3899 kPa. The temperature standard uncertainty, pressure standard uncertainty and density relative standard uncertainty was estimated to be 2.3 mK, 600 Pa and 0.0008, respectively. The experimental data shows good agreement with previous results. The HFO-1234ze(E) second and third virial coefficients were derived with the temperature of (363 to 401) K.
